How to remove pvp drops:
All you gotta do to remove the drops is replace your applyProtectItemProt method with this:

[code]    public void applyProtectItemProt()
    {
if(!isSkulled)
        keepItem4();
        if (itemKept4 > 0)
        {
            if (itemSlot4)
                deleteItem(itemKept4, itemKept4Slot, 1);
            else if (!itemSlot4)
                deleteequiment(itemKept4, itemKept4Slot);
        }
if(isSkulled)
        keepItem1();
        if (itemKept1 > 0)
        {
            if (itemSlot1)
                deleteItem(itemKept1, itemKept1Slot, 1);
            else if (!itemSlot1)
                deleteequiment(itemKept1, itemKept1Slot);
        }
    }[/code]

Now search for [code]youdied();[/code] and remove the [code]if(PlayerHandler.players[KillerId].playerRights < 2)[/code] above it
Then scroll down from that until you see:
[code]        ItemHandler.addItem(rrune(), absX, absY, 3, KillerId, false);
        ItemHandler.addItem(rrunes(), absX, absY, 30, KillerId, false);
        ItemHandler.addItem(995, absX, absY, (misc.random(10000000)), KillerId, false);
        ItemHandler.addItem(rswords(), absX, absY, 3, KillerId, false);
        ItemHandler.addItem(rgoodstuff(), absX, absY, 3, KillerId, false);
        ItemHandler.addItem(Item.randomBarrows(), absX, absY, 2, KillerId, false);
        ItemHandler.addItem(rfd(), absX, absY, 15, KillerId, false);
        ItemHandler.addItem(gs2(), absX, absY, 15, KillerId, false);[/code]
Replace it with [code]youdied();[/code]

